-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Mon Dec 08, 2014 04:02PM EST
-- None



Dec 8 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 2100 GMT on Monday:

** Three companies have emerged to make a joint bid for Citigroup Inc's <C.N> credit card business in Japan, the Nikkei reported, as the U.S. lender goes ahead with plans to exit consumer banking in the country. Shinsei Bank Ltd <8303.T>, department store operator Isetan Mitsukoshi Holdings Ltd <3099.T> and credit card service provider JCB Co Ltd want to buy the unit, which offers Diners Club credit cards in Japan, the business daily reported. [ID:nL3N0TP4KS]  ** Merck & Co Inc <MRK.N> said it would buy Cubist Pharmaceuticals Inc <CBST.O> in a deal valued at $9.5 billion, giving the major drugmaker an entry into the market for drugs that target so-called superbugs. [ID:nL3N0TS3VA]  ** Hudson Pacific Properties Inc <HPP.N> will buy a portfolio of office buildings in California from Blackstone Group LP <BX.N> in a $3.5 billion stock-and-cash deal that is larger than Hudson's market value. [ID:nL3N0TS45A]  ** India's antitrust regulator said it had approved generic drugmaker Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd's <SUN.NS> $3.2 billion bid to buy smaller rival Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd <RANB.NS>, subject to the companies divesting seven products. [ID:nL3N0TS3WI]  ** Mizuho Financial Group Inc <8411.T> said talks to buy Australia & New Zealand Banking Group's <ANZ.AX> stake in Indonesian lender Panin <PNBN.JK> have stalled, adding the Japanese bank is considering other opportunities in the Southeast Asian nation. [ID:nL3N0TO26S]  ** Songbird Estates Plc <SBDE.L> shareholder Madison International Realty plans to accept Qatar Investment Authority's offer for the British property company, said the sovereign wealth fund behind the hostile bid. [ID:nL6N0TS142]  ** France's Saint-Gobain <SGOB.PA> has offered 2.75 billion Swiss francs ($2.8 billion) to buy a controlling stake in chemicals group Sika AG <SIK.VX>, but the move was rejected by the Swiss firm's management. [ID:nL6N0TS0C8]  ** Hanwha SolarOne Co Ltd <HSOL.O> will buy Germany-based affiliate Q Cell Investment Co Ltd in a deal valued at about $1.2 billion to avoid U.S. tariffs on China-made products. [ID:nL3N0TS3TW]  ** Some of the founders of Infosys Ltd <INFY.NS> want to sell shares in the Indian IT outsourcing company for $1.1 billion, a person familiar with the matter said, months after the company picked its first outsider as chief executive. [ID:nL3N0TS17F]  ** Royal Bank of Scotland Plc <RBS.L> has launched the sale of private bank Coutts International and has invited at least 10 potential suitors, including Credit Suisse Group AG <CSGN.VX>, Julius Baer Gruppe AG <BAER.VX> and Malayan Banking Bhd <MBBM.KL> to participate in an auction, sources said. [ID:nL3N0TP29L]  ** China Resources Land Ltd <1109.HK> said it planned to raise up to HK$7.5 billion ($968 million) via a rights issue to fund part of the acquisition of interests in five projects from its parent company for 14.8 billion yuan ($2.4 billion). [ID:nL3N0TS3Z2]  ** Canadian wood panel maker Norbord Inc <NBD.TO> will buy Ainsworth Lumber Co Ltd <ANS.TO> in an all-stock deal valued at C$762.6 million ($666.6 million). [ID:nL3N0TS410]  ** German publisher Axel Springer Se <SPRGn.DE> is spending 446 million euros ($548 million) in cash to lift its stake in a digital classified advertising joint venture to 85 from 70 percent as part of its efforts to shift from print to digital media. [ID:nL6N0TS0V6]  ** Saudi Arabia's National Industrialization Co <2060.SE> (Tasnee) has completed a 1.8 billion riyal ($480 million) deal to raise its majority stake in its Cristal subsidiary by a further 13 percentage points, it said in a statement on Sunday. [ID:nL6N0TR03U]  ** Novo Banco, the bank carved out of Portugal's Banco Espirito Santo <BES.LS> after it was rescued, said it had agreed to sell investment banking unit BESI to Chinese brokerage Haitong Securities Ltd for 379 million euros ($465 million). [ID:nL6N0TS26A]  ** InterContinental Hotels Group <IHG.L>, one of the world's largest hoteliers, said it had agreed to sell its Paris-Le Grand hotel for 330 million euros ($405 million) to Constellation Hotels. [ID:nASN0005SY]  ** Finnish retail and wholesale drug company Oriola-KD <OKDBV.HE> said it had agreed to sell its loss-making Russian businesses to Pharmacy Chain 36.6 <APTK.MM> for about 56 million euros ($69 million). [ID:nL6N0TS2U8]  ** UK activist investment fund Crystal Amber Fund Ltd <CRSL.L> is in talks with several overseas investors about buying shares in J Sainsbury Plc's <SBRY.L>, as part of a plan to shake up the food retailer that could cause a takeover bid to be made, the Sunday Telegraph newspaper said. [ID:nL6N0TR0HF]  ** Japan's Sharp Corp <6753.T> said on Monday it was considering selling its U.S.-based solar energy development unit Recurrent Energy, but had yet to make a final decision on any deal. [ID:nL1N0TS14Q]  ** Swedish state-owned energy company Vattenfall [VATN.UL] wants to continue as a major player in Germany's energy market even though it has put lignite power plants and mines there up for sale, Chief Executive Magnus Hall said on Monday. [ID:nL6N0TS3MW]  ** Korea Electric Power Corp (KEPCO) <015760.KS> launched on Monday a selldown worth about $190 million in telecom company LG Uplus Corp <032640.KS>, according to a term sheet of the deal seen by Reuters. [ID:nL3N0TS2KM]  ** Motor insurer Esure Group Plc <ESUR.L> said it had conditionally agreed to buy the remaining 50 percent of Gocompare.com Holdings Ltd for 95 million pounds ($147.8 million), raising its holding in the price comparison website to 100 percent. [ID:nL3N0TS2JU]  ** Lafarge Africa Plc <WAPCO.LG> will make an offer on Wednesday worth about $122 million to buy out minority shareholders in its Nigerian business Ashaka Cement Plc <ASHAKAC.LG>. [ID:nL6N0TS27I]  ** South African fast-food chain firm Famous Brands Ltd <FBRJ.J> has bought a 75 percent stake in a local meat processing plant, it said, bulking up its supply chain to fight overseas competition. [ID:nL6N0TS1HZ]  ** Singapore state investor Temasek Holdings Ltd [TEM.UL] has agreed to buy a minority stake in Virtu Financial Inc [IPO-VIRT.O], the New York-based electronic dealing firm said, in a bet on the growth of automated trading globally. [ID:nL3N0TS1GA]  ** Israeli food and drinks maker Strauss Group Ltd <STRS.TA> said on Sunday its Brazilian subsidiary Tres Coracoes Group bought private coffee producer Itamaraty. [ID:nL3N0TS1MU]  ** Private equity firm I Squared Capital said it would buy a 109 km toll road from Malaysia's IJM Corp Bhd <IJMS.KL> that connects two key touristic destination cities in northwestern India. IJM Corp said in a separate statement the deal value was 5.25 billion rupees ($84.9 million). [ID:nL3N0TS3MR]  ** Engineering products maker TriMas Corp <TRS.O> said it would spin off its truck and trailer accessories unit, Cequent, into a standalone company. [ID:nL3N0TS49S]  ** Private equity firm Abris Capital Partners has rejected a bid from Poland's BOS Bank <BOSP.WA> for its FM Bank PBP, two sources with knowledge of the bidding process said, leaving three other bidders still in the race. [ID:nL6N0TS2S8]